com.quest.glue.api.services
Interface Credential

public interface Credential

A Credential defines authentication attributes for connecting to access controlled resources. These attributes are unencrypted in this form and should be handled in a controlled manner. Credentials should not cached or reused between authentication attempts and should always validate their assigned policies checkPolicies() and be released after their initial use release(boolean)

Since:
5.5.5.1

checkPolicies

void checkPolicies()
                   throws CredentialPolicyViolationException
Before attempting to authenticate using this Credential, the Agent must first check the assigned Policies for an violations. If these policies are all valid then the Credential maybe used.

Throws:
CredentialPolicyViolationException - if a Policy violation is encountered. Credential must be discarded
